    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-14T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-14T06:00:00-05:00" n="851"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d851">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.8890/3–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-14T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 14, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 14—6:27 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>875. Jardine-Matheson<note n="93" xml:id="d851fn93">British shipping firm.</note>
                    Shanghai received telegram March 11 from Tientsin agents not to despatch any
                    steamers Taku Bar pending issuance new Communist shipping regulations due
                    shortly. Their steamer had already left Hong Kong with Tientsin cargo aboard so
                    was diverted Pusan. Will proceed Tientsin later, if possible. However,
                    Butterfield and Swire Steamer <hi rend="italic">Hanyang</hi> also with Hong Kong
                    cargo expected arrive Taku about March 15. Butterfield and Swire state they have
                    no previous Communist clearance but are hopeful discharge possible. American
                    President Line will not send in another ship until Tientsin agent assures them
                    arrangements load outward cargo completed.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 875, repeated Nanking 520, Canton 156.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
